Mexico Cotton Production May Rise This Year, USDA Says

-- B y   E l i z a b e t h   C a m p b e l l
-- 
2011-03-18T19:10:34Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-18/mexico-cotton-production-may-rise-this-year-usda-says.html
  Mexico ’s cotton production may rise
to 683,000 bales in the year that ends July 31, up from an
estimated 411,000 bales the previous year, a unit of the U.S.
Department of Agriculture said.  Imports of the fiber will climb to 1.6 million bales this
season, up from an estimated 1.511 million a year earlier, the
agency’s  Foreign Agricultural Service  said in a  report  dated
March 15 and posted today on its website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Elizabeth Campbell in Chicago at 
